<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-6274] replaceNode improvements for XML processing</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-6274</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Groovy&apos;s XML processing has a few slightly inconsistent features and a small hole wrt replacing nodes.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The &lt;tt&gt;replaceNode(Closure)&lt;/tt&gt; method for &lt;tt&gt;DOMCategory&lt;/tt&gt; returns the last added node rather than the removed node (making it inconsistent with the built-in &lt;tt&gt;replaceChild&lt;/tt&gt; method) and equivalent methods for general collections (e.g. &lt;tt&gt;remove&lt;/tt&gt; for &lt;tt&gt;ArrayList&lt;/tt&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Ditto for the corresponding method in &lt;tt&gt;XmlParser&lt;/tt&gt;. Also, &lt;tt&gt;XmlParser&lt;/tt&gt; lacks a &lt;tt&gt;replaceNode(Node)&lt;/tt&gt; variant.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
